# Phase 5a: Annual Reporting Function

## Objective

Build a reporting function that produces a single annual report document
covering all years of the simulation run. This is a first-class business
process, not a diagnostic tool. It will evolve through a feedback and
improvement backlog, with Rich providing steering on prioritisation.

## Context

The simulation has completed a full 9.5-year run (2016–mid 2025) with the
following layers active: dual-fuel portfolio (electricity + gas), multi-tenor
hedging with risk committee governance, weather-driven demand, cost to serve,
churn model, Shifted-BG CLV, home move win rate, and enterprise value
function. 243 tests passing.

The problem: there is currently no way for Rich (as MD/board) to read what
happened to the business across those years. Numbers exist in summary files
but there is no coherent narrative or structured reporting that a company
operator would actually use.

## Deliverable 1 — v1 Annual Report

Produce a single document: `docs/reports/ANNUAL_REPORT.md`

One section per calendar year (2016 through 2024, plus partial 2025 if data
exists). Each year section must contain:

**Trading & Risk**
- Opening and closing treasury
- Net margin (total, electricity, gas split)
- Wholesale cost vs tariff revenue
- Hedge fraction at start of year and average across year
- Number of risk committee interventions (Context Handshake wake-ups)
- VaR ratio: current vs stressed floor
- Worst single period loss and when it occurred

**Customer Book**
- Customers on supply at start and end of year
- Acquisitions and losses (churn + home move) during year
- Segment breakdown (resi/SME, electricity/gas/dual)
- Average CLV across book at year end
- Highest and lowest CLV customer
- Bill shock events: count and which customers affected
- Churn risk: how many customers above threshold at year end

**Pricing & Margin**
- Tariff rates in effect (or range if changed during year)
- Average margin per customer per MWh
- Cost to serve per customer (average and range)
- Net margin per customer after cost to serve
- Activity-based pricing flag: any customers net-negative?

**Portfolio Health**
- Capital cost ratio
- Treasury drawdown events (>10% threshold)
- Service quality score
- Any regulatory threshold breaches

**Year narrative (3-4 sentences):** What happened to this business this year?
What was the dominant risk or opportunity? What did the risk committee do?

The document should open with a one-page executive summary covering the full
9.5-year arc: how the business started, survived the 2021-2022 crisis, and
what its current financial position and enterprise value represent.

Format: clean markdown, readable without a renderer. Numbers to 2 decimal
places. Years as H2 headers. No raw data dumps — synthesised figures only.

## Deliverable 2 — Reporting Improvement Backlog

Immediately after generating v1, produce `docs/reports/REPORTING_BACKLOG.md`

This is the agent's own assessment of what v1 is missing, what a real energy
supplier's board pack would contain that this doesn't, and what improvements
would most increase the report's usefulness to Rich as operator and advisor.

Format each backlog item as:
- **Item:** what it is
- **Value:** why it matters to a company operator
- **Effort:** Low / Medium / High (token + GPU cost estimate)
- **Depends on:** any data or features not yet built

Aim for 10-15 items. Prioritise by value/effort ratio. Flag any items that
require new simulation data to be generated (e.g. HH smart meter customers,
competitor pricing) vs items that can be built from existing run output.

End the backlog with a section: **What Rich needs to decide** — any items
where the right answer depends on a strategic choice only Rich can make.

## Deliverable 3 — Report Generator as Standing Function

The report must not be a one-off script. Implement as:

`saas/reporting/annual_report.py`

A callable function that reads from the existing simulation output and
produces the full annual report document. It should be runnable at any time
to regenerate the report from current data.

Add `make report` to the Makefile as a target that runs this and writes the
output to `docs/reports/ANNUAL_REPORT.md`.

Tests: at minimum, assert the function runs without error and produces a
non-empty document with the correct year sections present.

## Constraints

- Read only from existing simulation output — do not re-run the simulation
- Do not invent numbers — if data for a metric doesn't exist in the output,
  say so explicitly in the report rather than estimating
- The report is for a human operator, not for another model — write it that way
- Delegate all code generation to local Qwen

